description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THIS POST IS FIXED TERM/SECONDMENT FOR 18 MONTHS DUE TO MEET THE NEEDS OF THE SERVICE. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IF YOU ARE INTERESTED IN APPLYING FOR THE SECONDMENT POSITION, YOU MUST OBTAIN PERMISSION FROM YOUR CURRENT LINE MANAGER PRIOR TO APPLYING FOR THIS POST. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An excellent opportunity has arisen for a suitably qualified and experienced Healthcare Support Worker to join the Wound Clinic Service. The applicant must be confident and competent in a wide range of clinical skills. There is a requirement for a flexible approach to work and for ability to travel between sites in a timely manner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The applicant will hold Level 3 NVQ/QSF in a health care associated certificate,skills, knowledge and experience to equivalent level.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is based with the Wound Clinic Service, which are located in DSH, YCR, YCC and KHHP, across all four localities within Cwm Taf University Health Board.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 12/11/2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Team Leader Melissa Duffy or Deputy Team leaders Danielle Clark/Sarah Pugh on&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01685 351494&lt;/p&gt;
